<p>Yo what’s up guys! The goddamned COVID-19 goes viral in recent days. Hope that we can eliminate this little bastard in near future, and I sincerely hope
everything goes well with you and your family.</p>

<p>This winter I travelled to Japan with my parents and girlfriend. We went to Hokkaido and Honshu Island. From snowy Sapporo to windy Kamakura, from Kyoto shrines to Tokyo skyscrapers, I deeply felt the 
beauty of this civilized country. Japan is blended with traditional assets and modern technology, with natural resources and artificial manufacture, with external reserve and hidden craziness. Very attractive.</p>

<blockquote>
  <p>Hokkaido</p>
</blockquote>

<p>Hokkaido is a place that can intepret my imagination of the World of Snow. It has both modern cities like Sapporo and quiet towns like Toya. People here
enjoy beer, ski and seafood.</p>

