<blockquote>
  <p>Honshu</p>
</blockquote>

<p>The famous Osaka, Kyoto &amp; Tokyo are all in Honshu. Big cities like Tokyo are much more crowded than Hokkaido little towns. However, Japanese traditions are well preserved in Honshu.
You can explore shrines, temples, the culture of Kimoni and Japanese food in Honshu. Last minute you may be walking along thousands of people at crossroad in Shibuya, Tokyo, the next
minute you may say your prayer in the temples. Marvelous experience!</p>

